{
  "stem": "3964.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 17.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they deposited us, or unloaded us, in a huge hall, where we found approximately 600 or 700 other Jewish people from other communities, as well as from Kassel, who had been told they were gonna be resettled-- no beds, no mattresses, just our little suitcase and us in his large hall, which was a [NON-ENGLISH], which was a gymnastics hall-- parquet floor.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And nobody knew really what was going on-- a lot of panic, a lot of panic.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And what's your destiny?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, you don't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some rumors went around that we were going here, or there, or somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was-- it was-- it was terrible.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was-- I mean, it was an exposure for me which just words cannot describe-- old people, 60s and their 70s, children, babies, commotion, crying, no food, no water, sleeping on the floor, more Jews coming.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What's going on?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Nobody knows.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, it's-- it's-- if you know what's-- what you're up against, you know, you can deal with it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the unknown-- the unknown is the mystery in life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And after what had been happening, we really weren't sure what they were up to.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We hadn't heard about concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had heard about [NON-ENGLISH], which is resettling.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we never heard from those people who had been resettled.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they must have been all right.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Otherwise, we would have heard from them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Anyhow, we were in this hall for two days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We did get some food and some water.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Sanitary conditions were fairly decent, because the Germans didn't want to have their hall messed up.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they made sure that we went to the toilets and bathrooms.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They, again, got us up one morning.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
